    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Tour De Fun!]]></title>
    <link href="http://njbiddle.com/blog/2014/02/09/tour-de-fun-splash/"/>
    <updated>2014-02-09T18:14:03-06:00</updated>
    <id>http://njbiddle.com/blog/2014/02/09/tour-de-fun-splash</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://tourdefun.net/">Tour De Fun</a> 2014 is quickly approaching, and so is a site redesign. Web/real-life wizard <a href="http://nicinabox.com/">Nic Aitch</a> is helping me build a ruby on rails info app and so far, it&rsquo;s been great.</p>

<br>


<p><img src="images/TDF/TDF.png" alt="TDF" /></p>

<!--more-->


<p>We&rsquo;re using Active Admin and a gem by Nic called <a href="https://github.com/nicinabox/petrie">Petrie</a> for content management. This lets other users on the Tour De Fun team edit content, bands, venues, and set times.</p>

<br>


<p><img src="images/TDF/TDF2.png" alt="TDF Management" /></p>

<br>


<p>Hosting is done through <a href="http://heroku.com/">Heroku</a> for simplicity&rsquo;s sake, and managed with git. Track progress through my <a href="http://github.com/NJBiddle/tourdefun">github</a>!</p>

<br>


<p><img src="images/TDF/TDF3.png" alt="TDF Heroku" /></p>

<br>



]]></content>
